<h1>Configure Your Google Developer Account</h1>
<p>
  First off, you need a developer account at google (and a normal Google account).
</p>
<p>
  <b>Please note that some of the APIs only work with HTTPS. So I hightly recommend to set this up on your server</b>
</p>

<h2>Step 1 - Set up account and project</h2>
<p>
  <a href="https://console.developers.google.com/project">Go here to make one</a>.
  Then create a new project named "OS.js".
</p>

<h2>Step 2 - Set up credentials</h2>
<p>
  Find the "Credentials" menu entry (left side). Create a new OAuth Client ID.
  The "Client ID" is what you will be using to configure support.
</p>

<h2>Step 3 - Enable API modules</h2>
<p>
  Find the "APIs" menu entry (left side). Then click on the APIs you want to enable.
</p>
<p>
  These are the modules that OS.js uses:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Contacts API</li>
  <li>Gmail API</li>
  <li>Google+ API</li>
  <li>Drive API</li>
</ul>

<h1>Adding Google API and VFS support</h1>

<p>
  Simply create a config file to enable both API and VFS. Ex <b>src/conf/901-gapi.json</b>:
</p>
<pre class="code">
{
  "client" : {
    "GoogleAPI": {
      "ClientId": "INSERT YOUR CLIENT ID HERE"
    },

    "VFS": {
      "GoogleDrive": {
        "Enabled": true
      }
    }
  }
}
</pre>


<p>
  Then run:
</p>
<pre>grunt config</pre>
